-- Fondiaria Sai Invites Offers to Purchase Velasca Tower Property in Milan
-- Armorel Kenna
-- 2010-07-21T07:18:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/milan-s-velasca-tower-is-offered-for-sale-by-the-ligresti-family-s-company.html

          
          
             Fondiaria Sai SpA , the insurer
controlled by Italy’s Ligresti family, is seeking bids to
purchase the Torre Velasca property in central Milan.  
 The building, which is one-third empty, could generate as
much as 5.3 million euros ($6.8 million) of annual rental
income, according to the Milan-based company’s website.
Fondiaria Sai’s unit Immobiliare Lombarda SpA is assisting the
insurer on the sale.  
 The 27-floor mushroom-shaped tower, completed in 1958,
houses shops, offices, apartments and has two of floors of car
parking and storage space.  Offers  for the property must be made
by Sept. 24.  
